			<div class="content" id="post-content-3598559">
									

<p><em>What would you do to save the world?</em></p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;So&nbsp;much&nbsp;credit&nbsp;is&nbsp;due</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>I had tons of help with this from pretty much the entire site. Everyone below is partially responsible for these atrocities:</p>
<p>Zyn for encouragement at the idea and brainstorming stage.</p>
<p>Modern_Erasmus, psul, Zyn, and everyone else on the message board about Scranton Reality Anchor - all the ideas about that helped tie together the atmosphere.</p>
<p>Scorpion451, psul, and Petrograd helped out with great insight into the horrifyingly real world of brain-in-a-jar experiments.</p>
<p>Modern_Erasmus, DrChandra, and Kakroom for checking it out as a draft, I truly appreciate that.</p>
<p>Everyone in chat who indulged me in bullshitting about Hume levels. Jarvis for generating most of the names, keep up the good work J-dog.</p>
<p>Credit is also due to the author of SCP-2003; this all started when I read that a couple weeks ago and got hit with this mental picture of a kindhearted doctor saying soothing things into someone's ear as she cuts their brain out.</p>
<p>And to the author of the keter cakes, I hope it's okay that I used your thing here. It's a classic.</p>
<p>Also, thanks to everyone who read and/or commented on this so far and everyone who does going forward. I would never have written this if you weren't here to read it.</p>
<p>Even after all this, the following pun is the most disgusting thing I've ever written:</p>
<p>There's so much Mo to come.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

